THE PILOT RPRTD THAT DURING A LANDING, THE AIRCRAFT BALLOONED BEFORE 
TOUCHDOWN. HE SAID HE TRIED TO LEVEL THE PLANE, BUT IT TOUCHED DOWN, 
NOSEWHEEL FIRST. IT THEN PORPORPOISED SEVERAL TIMES AND THE NOSE GEAR 
COLLAPSED. BEFORE STOPPING, THE AIRCRAFT SKIDDED OFF THE RIGHT SIDE OF THE 
RUNWAY AND WAS FURTHER DAMAGED. 
PILOT'S IMPROPER FLARE AND IMPROPER RECOVERY FROM A BOUNCED LANDING, 
WHICH RESULTED IN A PORPOISE. 
